<br>
Spells nedded: Flash of light, root, stuns, center lign of spells(daring...), healing spells, spook the dead, cancel magic.<br>
<br>
Tactics: <br>
<br>
Against casters: when a pet is present, root the pet(or in the case of a necro, fear it), root the caster, the caster is now as good as dead. Make sure to interrupt as many spells as possible and remove any damage shields. Flash of light isnt very useful as any smart caster would have his spells hotkeyed. Casters are pretty easy prey.<br>
<br>
Against melee classes: Remove all their buffs, root, and either use flash of light and circle strafe behind them and hack them to bits where they can't touch you, or if you are high enough and have a deepwater bracer, you can probably keep them stunned at least 50% of the time. Against a melee class I would suggest getting as much AC and HP gear as possible. LoH may be needed.<br>
<br>
Against bards: Jump off the highest nearby structure to kill yourself, better loose the EXP then stand their watching you health get drained and not be able to do anything about it. I don't think it is possible for an equal level paladin to kill a bard unless the bard is a total putz. <p><center>~~<u>Aziraphale Crowley</u>~~</center>
