<br>
Stand next to a guard when they use their aoe dot.  No you probably won't win but they will most likely zone or go ld and die if they continue to fight.<br>
<br>
Or: stand next to various green npcs that cause faction loss when killed.<br>
<br>
Or:  just get in a crowded area and fight.  Bard songs draw aggro like mad so if you can just get enough mobs on him at one time he'll probably crash from video lag and/or not be able to move well :P.<br>
<br>
Or:  If you are dueling in an area where none of the above will work, spam him with jboots until he goes ld :P. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utheskyfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Skyfyre</A> at: 11/3/00 9:34:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/udolphinoceansinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dolphin Oceansinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/5/00 11:13:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling as a Paladin</span><hr size=1> Ok Khaedron, you are on!!!  Anywhere, Anytime!!! =)<br>
